BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:P7_pNbAWpttVHEpqumsUn
SUMMARY:Seed Starting Tips and Techniques
DTSTAMP:20260318T234515Z
DTSTART:20260328T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Taught by Nancy Kartes and Bill Thorness. Our mild late winter 
	allows us to sprout the edible garden early. Getting growing now will mean
	 longer harvests and more use of our garden throughout the year. Learn wha
	t can be started now\, whether to choose seeds or starts\, where to site y
	our early spring garden\, how to know when the soil is ready\, and how to 
	plan ahead for the best success. Hands-on lessons will also teach you how 
	to make a “seed snail\,” how to use a soil block\, and how to make your ow
	n seed-starting mix! You’ll also go home with some early-season seeds read
	y to sprout. $24.50 BBGS Member/$35 Non-Member.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcit
	y.com/events/#/details/seed-starting-tips-and-techniques/17923225/2026-03-
	28T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Learning & Education
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/seed-starting-tips-and-te
	chniques/17923225/2026-03-28T00
LOCATION:Bellevue Botanical Garden\, 12001 Main St\, Bellevue\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-learning
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Learning & Education
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:CjB-idz3Nrh6jbBOj2xWg
SUMMARY:Figure/Ground: New Criteria
DTSTAMP:20260318T234515Z
DTSTART:20260328T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Figure/Ground: New Criteria is inspired by cultural historian S
	arah Lewis’s concept of “groundwork aesthetics\,” exploring figure-ground 
	relationships and their connection to social tension. It builds on Lewis’s
	 work\, which—set against the expansion of Stand Your Ground laws across t
	he United States since 2005\, laws that broadly define rights to use letha
	l self-defense against perceived threats—describes a range of artistic int
	erventions that reimagine “the literal and figurative meaning of ground.” 
	Primarily featuring works from the Henry collection created in the twenty-
	first century\, Figure/Ground reflects a period in which hard-won civil ri
	ghts and claims to self-determination have been eroded across the US\, dis
	proportionately affecting Black\, Brown\, LGBTQ\\+\, and other marginalize
	d communities.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/figure-gro
	und-new-criteria/17923441/2026-03-28T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civ
	ic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/figure-ground-new-criteri
	a/17923441/2026-03-28T00
LOCATION:Henry Art Gallery\, 15th Ave NE & 41st St\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
